THIRD-PARTY LICENSES AND ACKNOWLEDGMENTS

This project incorporates several open-source libraries and tools. We acknowledge
and are grateful to the developers of the following projects:

Core Framework & Runtime:
- Next.js (MIT License) - React framework for production
- React (MIT License) - JavaScript library for building user interfaces
- Node.js (MIT License) - JavaScript runtime environment
- TypeScript (Apache-2.0 License) - Typed superset of JavaScript

Styling & UI Components:
- Tailwind CSS (MIT License) - Utility-first CSS framework
- Shadcn/ui (MIT License) - Re-usable components built with Radix UI
- Radix UI (MIT License) - Low-level UI primitives
- Framer Motion (MIT License) - Motion library for React
- Lucide React (ISC License) - Beautiful & consistent icon toolkit

Analysis & Automation:
- Lighthouse (Apache-2.0 License) - Automated auditing for web apps
- Puppeteer (Apache-2.0 License) - Node.js API for Chrome/Chromium
- Cheerio (MIT License) - Server-side implementation of jQuery
- Axios (MIT License) - Promise-based HTTP client

Development & Build Tools:
- ESLint (MIT License) - JavaScript linting utility
- PostCSS (MIT License) - CSS transformation tool
- Autoprefixer (MIT License) - CSS vendor prefixing

Email & Communication:
- Nodemailer (MIT License) - Email sending library for Node.js

Data Visualization:
- Chart.js (MIT License) - Simple yet flexible charting library
- React Chart.js 2 (MIT License) - React wrapper for Chart.js
- Recharts (MIT License) - Composable charting library

Form Handling & Validation:
- React Hook Form (MIT License) - Performant forms with easy validation
- Zod (MIT License) - TypeScript-first schema validation

PDF Generation:
- jsPDF (MIT License) - Client-side PDF generation
- html2canvas (MIT License) - Screenshots with JavaScript

Utilities:
- clsx (MIT License) - Utility for constructing className strings
- class-variance-authority (Apache-2.0 License) - CVA for component variants
- tailwind-merge (MIT License) - Merge Tailwind CSS classes

